subject: Enable BR Keyword check on system VPD
commitMessage:
Enable BR Keyword check on system VPD

restoreSystemVPD  checks for BR keyword to get the BRAND of the system.
Curently supported Brands are S0 and D0.
For each brand, we have some set of keywords to verify that
it's value is not blank in the VPD, also should have valid value.

Test Result-

root@rainier:/tmp# ./ibm-read-vpd -f /sys/bus/i2c/drivers/at24/8-0050/eeprom
Read BR: S0
RBkwVal[0]:
Found keyword value invalid OR not supported...breaking

as RB data is blank in the VPD, we are breaking here.
Also, forced to continue with blank RB value-

root@rainier:/tmp# ./ibm-read-vpd -f /sys/bus/i2c/drivers/at24/8-0050/eeprom

Read BR: S0
RBkwVal[0]:
isKwValid: 1
sys Brand: S0_BRAND
Setting GPIO: SLOT0_PRSNT_EN_RSVD to 1
Binding device 4-0050

Change-Id: Id349357f06f72486b5fac4c53bf024827e152d8d
Signed-off-by: Alpana Kumari <alpankum@in.ibm.com>
